methods.name: is_stale
methods.docstring:
Is the cache stale for the given resource?

:param resource: The :class:`Resource` being cached.
:param path: The path of the resource in the cache.
:return: True if the cache is stale.

methods.name: get
methods.docstring:
Get a resource into the cache,

:param resource: A :class:`Resource` instance.
:return: The pathname of the resource in the cache.

classes.name: Resource
classes.docstring:
A class representing an in-package resource, such as a data file. This is
not normally instantiated by user code, but rather by a
:class:`ResourceFinder` which manages the resource.

methods.name: as_stream
methods.docstring:
Get the resource as a stream.

This is not a property to make it obvious that it returns a new stream
each time.

classes.name: ResourceFinder
classes.docstring: Resource finder for file system resources.

classes.name: ZipResourceFinder
classes.docstring: Resource finder for resources in .zip files.

functions.name: finder
functions.docstring:
Return a resource finder for a package.
:param package: The name of the package.
:return: A :class:`ResourceFinder` instance for the package.

functions.name: finder_for_path
functions.docstring:
Return a resource finder for a path, which should represent a container.

:param path: The path.
:return: A :class:`ResourceFinder` instance for the path.
